reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2019
reviews.reviewText: Update** the seller asked that I ship them the tablet and they would issue me a refund. I asked for the issue to be fixed or a replacement tablet. They decided to issue me a refund after a charge for a restocking fee. They claimed that they were able to add a samsung account after a factory reset. Before I sent back the tablet, I was on the phone with Samsung for nearly an hour and could not resolve the issue with a factory reset through the settings options or a hard factory reset. I was able to get a full refund from square trade though. I would not trust buying from the seller overstock planet again.**This tablet is great but I cannot log in and register the device on my Samsung account as the new owner. I get the error "processing failed". According to Samsung, this means that the original user deleted their account from the device but did not log into a computer and delete the device from theirsamsung account online. Without the original owner doing this the device is considered stolen and they cannot over ride this. If I were to do a factory reset, the device would be rendered useless because I would need the original account to get past the setup mode. I have contacted the seller and am hoping they can contact the original owner. If not I will need to get this tablet replaced to register as the new owner. I will update my review once the seller contacts me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 24, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Buyer beware. I bought 2.
reviews.reviewText: I bought two of these and as much as I wish I could give this item 5 stars I'll have to give 3 for these reasons:Yes, I understand these tablets are refurbished and one tablet is perfect. Charges perfectly, connects to Wi-Fi perfectly, functions perfectly, no complaints. Second tablet on the other hand is working fine except for the eissue that when it came to charging it, there is a red x over the battery icon. I messaged the seller and the have good costumer service and replayed within a few hours of me messaging but the only thing I was told was to contact Samsung for more help with the issue. Second table also does not hold the charge for long. I use it and within 2-4 hours I have to recharge it all over again.Other than the issue with the second tablet, the packing was great, delivery was fast and they have good costumer service but I definitely suggest you go ahead and spend the extra money on a new one because although these are certified refurbished, you're pretty much gambling with what you are getting.Overall, I am satisfied but I'm not gonna waste my time returning one tablet or trying to get my money back.
